gomodel:SYNGO_3986  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Prohibitin immunoreactivity colocalizes with presynaptic (Bassoon) and postsynaptic (Shank 3) marker proteins in cortical primary cultures.\n\n12/01/2021 Dnyanada: The additional literature (PMID: 23622064) identifies prohibitin in presynaptic active zone fraction. The confocal images used in the annotated paper do not have the resolution to discriminate between pre- and postsynaptic localisation. Due to a lack of strong experimental evidence in favour of either the presynapse or postsynapse, the SynGO term \"synapse\" was used.. Experimental description: All rats were 12 weeks old when the experiments were started. p. 879" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3986" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

